String str = "Hello, World!";
byte[] bytes = str.getBytes();

This will give you a byte array that represents the string in the default encoding of the platform. If you want to specify a different encoding, you can do so like this:
byte[] bytes = str.getBytes("UTF-8");

This will give you a byte array that represents the string in UTF-8 encoding.

